## Phase 2 – Foundational ✅

⚠️ CRITICAL: All story phases depend on this foundation.

- [x] T005 [P] [US8] Implement tree validator in `src/utils/validation.ts` — enforce 23-item limit, throw on invalid node types
- [x] T006 [P] [US8] Implement localStorage helpers in `src/utils/storage.ts` — read/write with error fallback to defaults
- [x] T007 [P] [US8] Create shadow DOM mount entry point in `src/index.ts` — append to `document.body`
- [x] T008 [P] [US8] Write Playwright contract tests for validator (valid tree, 24-item throw, invalid type throw)

**Checkpoint**: `import DirNav from 'dirnav'; DirNav(tree)` mounts a shadow DOM node on the page; validator correctly rejects bad trees.

---

## Phase 3 – US1: Floating Window ✅

**Goal**: Draggable, resizable window with persistent position/size.
**Independent Test**: Drag → move → resize → close → reopen → position/size restored.

- [x] T009 [P] [US1] Create `Window.tsx` — title bar drag handler using pointer events; CSS transforms for smooth movement
- [x] T010 [P] [US1] Add resize handle (bottom-right corner) to `Window.tsx`
- [x] T011 [P] [US1] Wire `WindowState` signals in `DirnavUI.tsx`; default to 25vw × 25vh centered
- [x] T012 [P] [US1] Add close (X) and resize-to-default (□) buttons to title bar
- [x] T013 [P] [US1] Persist window position + size to localStorage via `createEffect`; restore on mount
- [x] T014 [P] [US1] Write Playwright tests: drag, resize, close/reopen persistence, reset-to-default

**Checkpoint**: Window is independently usable; position/size round-trips through localStorage.

---

## Phase 4 – US2 + US3: Navigation Controls & Directory Display ✅

**Goal**: Title bar dynamic controls + breadcrumbs + paginated item list.
**Independent Test**: Navigate deep → truncated breadcrumbs appear → click breadcrumb → jump to level → 10-item dir → pagination dots appear.

- [x] T015 [P] [US2] Create `TitleBar.tsx` — show back (←) when not at root, show (>) at root; centered directory name
- [x] T016 [P] [US2] Wire back button to navigate up one level in `DirnavUI.tsx`
- [x] T017 [P] [US3] Create `NavigationView.tsx` — render numbered item list (1–9 per page)
- [x] T018 [P] [US3] Implement breadcrumb bar — full path ≤4 levels, `... > parent > current` beyond
- [x] T019 [P] [US3] Implement pagination — max 3 pages; item 1 = prev page; item 9 = next page; dots indicator
- [x] T020 [P] [US2] [US3] Write Playwright tests: back button visibility, breadcrumb truncation, pagination

**Checkpoint**: Directory tree navigable by mouse only; breadcrumbs and pagination work correctly.

---

## Phase 5 – US4: Keyboard Shortcuts ✅

**Goal**: Full keyboard control with global event listener.
**Independent Test**: Ctrl+` toggle → 1–9 select → Backspace back → Esc hide → `` ` `` command palette.

- [x] T021 [US4] Attach global `keydown` listener on `document` in `DirnavUI.tsx`; remove on cleanup
- [x] T022 [P] [US4] Implement Ctrl+` toggle (show / hide / focus) with focus-state tracking
- [x] T023 [P] [US4] Implement 1–9 item selection (also handles page-turn at boundaries)
- [x] T024 [P] [US4] Implement Backspace (navigate up) and Esc (hide) handlers
- [x] T025 [P] [US4] Implement `` ` `` key to open command palette when at root and focused
- [x] T026 [P] [US4] Write Playwright tests for each keyboard shortcut and edge cases (no items, at root, etc.)

**Checkpoint**: Entire component operable with keyboard only; no mouse needed after Ctrl+` shows window.

---

## Phase 6 – US5: Command Palette & Fuzzy Search ✅

**Goal**: Fuzzy search across all leaf nodes with keyboard navigation.
**Independent Test**: Open palette → type partial name → sorted results → Arrow keys move selection → Enter activates → resets to root → Esc behavior correct.

- [x] T027 [US5] Create `CommandPalette.tsx` — search input + scrollable result list with selection highlight
- [x] T028 [P] [US5] Implement fuzzy search + relevance scoring in `src/utils/fuzzy.ts`
- [x] T029 [P] [US5] Wire fuzzy search to command palette: debounced on input change, sorted results
- [x] T030 [P] [US5] Implement Arrow Up/Down result navigation; Enter activates + resets to root
- [x] T031 [P] [US5] Implement Esc: non-empty → clear search; empty → exit palette + hide window
- [x] T032 [P] [US5] Write Playwright tests: partial match, result order, keyboard nav, Esc behavior

**Checkpoint**: Command palette independently testable — activates items and resets state correctly.

---

## Phase 7 – US6: Node Type Handlers ✅

**Goal**: Four node types each dispatch correctly.
**Independent Test**: All four node types in one tree → each behaves per spec.

- [x] T033 [P] [US6] Implement directory node selection → push path and render children
- [x] T034 [P] [US6] Implement action node → call `callback()` on selection
- [x] T035 [P] [US6] Implement input node → inline edit, Enter saves to localStorage, Esc cancels
- [x] T036 [P] [US6] Implement virtual directory node → call async `action()`, show loader, render result
- [x] T037 [P] [US6] Add virtual directory error handling — display error, maintain previous state
- [x] T038 [P] [US6] Write Playwright tests for all four node types including virtual error scenario

**Checkpoint**: Mixed node tree navigable; all four types behave per spec acceptance scenarios.

---

## Phase 8 – US7: Theme and Meta Settings ✅

**Goal**: Light/Dark/System theme switchable via command palette only, persisted.
**Independent Test**: Open palette → select theme → applies immediately → reload → theme restored.

- [x] T039 [P] [US7] Add theme signal to `DirnavUI.tsx`; wire CSS custom properties to shadow DOM root
- [x] T040 [P] [US7] Implement System theme detection via `prefers-color-scheme` media query
- [x] T041 [P] [US7] Inject theme meta-items into command palette results (not in main nav tree)
- [x] T042 [P] [US7] Persist selected theme to localStorage; restore on mount
- [x] T043 [P] [US7] Write Playwright tests: theme switch applies immediately, persists across reload

**Checkpoint**: Theme options appear in command palette only; selection persists and applies in real time.

